      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The Emma Stewart barn looks to dominate this race with four runners, all of them last-start winners. COMEANDSEE (2) has been impressive in leading from wider barriers to win her two starts so far by big margins, the latest by 15m at Maryborough. Can take advantage of the low draw to maintain the perfect record. KAHULA (1) comes through the Nutrien Classic Sales race series where she was a closing second from the back row when making her debut in the heats before cruising home by 14.5m in the final at Listed level, again from the second line. On the up and should get the favours from the inside draw. CARDIGAN SNIPER (7) cops a wide draw but he looks talented having led from a similar barrier to cruise home by close to 15m when making his debut at Bendigo and should only be better for the experience. SOME HIGH (5) switches back to the mainland following a winning debut at Hobart where he raced parked before getting home by 3m.",
